Flip a coin. If heads, put 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your hand.

data.name: Rare Candy
rules: You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

"Choose 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. If you have a Stage 2 card in your hand that evolves from that Pokémon, put that card onto the Basic Pokémon to evolve it. You cant use this card during your first turn or on a Basic Pokémon that was put into play this turn."

data.name: Life Herb
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your Pokémon, and remove all Special Conditions and 6 damage counters from that Pokémon (all if there are less than 6).

data.name: Friend Ball
rules: "Choose 1 of your opponents Pokémon. Search your deck for a Baby Pokémon, Basic Pokémon, or Evolution card of the same type (color), show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward."

data.name: PokéNav
rules: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck, and choose a Basic Pokémon, Evolution card, or Energy card. Show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. Put the 2 other cards back on top of your deck in any order.

data.name: Switch
rules: You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).
Switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Lure Ball
rules: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, choose an Evolution card from your discard pile, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.

data.name: Underground Expedition
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Look at the 4 cards from the bottom of your deck. Choose any 2 cards there and put them into your hand. Put the remaining cards back on the bottom of your deck in any order.

rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
